<Author>peggyppk1
<Content>Great Place and Staff I stayed at this hotel one night before a cruise. The room and bathroom are very clean and the bed very comfortable. I booked this hotel based on the reviews on Tripadvisor and am glad I did. I made the reservation months in advance directly with the hotel and when I noticed the lower rates on their website near the travel date I called and they honored the lower price without giving me any trouble. I had called several other times regarding the shuttle to the port and the person I spoke to everytime was always helpful and polite. I did not notice any flight noises even though the location of the hotel is probably directly in the flight path. Be aware that the hotel van picks up on the departure level instead of the arrival level. If we had not called the hotel we would have been waiting forever at the wrong place! We waited about 30 min for the van but had no trouble recognizing it. Everyone at the hotel, the staff at the reception desk and breakfast room, the driver, etc. seemed happy to help. We were offered rides to nearby restaurants in the van but decided to take a walk after a 4+ hour flight from the west coast. Had a very nice dinner at the 94th Aero Squadron about a 10 min walk up the street. You can see the small planes take off out your window - no noise!! Breakfast was not gourmet Sunday brunch but adequate to kickstart the day - omelets, ham, pastries and breads, cereals, fruits, yogurt,juices coffee and teas. The shuttle to the port was on time and took about 10 min. I agree with the other reviewers that the staff at this hotel gives the impression they actually like having you there! This is probably not the place to stay for a vacation but for short Miami stops I would definitely recommend this hotel. 
