<Content>Very pleasant experience in Miami I recently stayed 5 nights at the Miami Airport Hampton and agreed with prior reviews that this is a very pleasant place to stay. I stayed in the King Suite (#1001) and was pleased with the size of the room. It had a great view of the lagoon and Miami airport. For those of you who love to watch aircraft, you will be very happy here indeed. The windows were sound-proofed keeping it very quiet despite the busy airport nearby.The room was kept very clean. Was it perfect? No, not quite and the carpeting could use a freshening-up but ioverall, the room felt quite clean to me. The bathroom was kept spotless, I must say.The bed was much better than average. Firm and soft at the same time and without the annoying sinking, depression at the head of bed which is so common with most hotel beds.The stafff here is the best. A totally opposite attitude that one gets at S. Beach. Here, the staff actually smiles and goes out of their way to make you feel comfortable and at home. I was given directions whenever I needed them and received a great recommendation for a local barbershop, where I got a fantastic haircut.Regarding the location, it is a quick 15 minute drive to S. Beach. I have stayed at S. Beach many times and prefer this location after this visit due to the more open, less congested feel, the proximity to other destinations such as Coral Gables and most of all the friendly staff. If you are a party animal and want close access to the bars and clubs on S. Beach, this is not the place for you. If you want a relaxing, clean place to stay in this tropical location, this is a very good choice. Though this may be a slightly more expensive Hampton than other cities, this is to be expected given the very expensive Miami and S. Beach market. Overall, this represents a much better value than most properties on S. Beach.I highly recommend this place and will definitely stay here again when in Miami. 
