<Content>Comfortable Pre-Cruise Night Stay My husband and I stayed for one night (June 8) at this wonderful hotel for a pre-cruise stay. It met my expectations and more. Our flight arrived early in the day so we called from the airport to let them know we would need to be picked up (there is a complimentary van shuttle to and from the airport to the hotel) and if our room would be ready for us. I read the confirmation number I was given over the phone and was told everything was ready and waiting for our arrival, exactly what we requested, no problems. The air conditioned shuttle ride from the airport to the hotel took less than 15 mins at noontime, which was great. The hotel is is in a 'pretty good' neighborhood; it's across the street literally from a mini-mall w/ a Publix grocery store, CVS, Walgreens, etc (in case you need sundries, food, etc) but if you're looking for the Miami/South Beach you see on TV, this is not the area. That said, check in was perfect, the pool area was nice and clean. The room is basic but has all you need for your stay - very comfortable bed, white soft down bedding, toiletries, hairdryer, clean bathroom/shower, couldn't have been more satisfied w/ our one night stay. We had a view of the airport and could watch planes come and go - but never heard any plane noise from inside our room, which was great. Breakfast was fantastic - a complimentary hot breakfast w/ eggs, sausage, biscuits, and then cereal, yogurt, danish, fruit, coffee/tea, juice, etc. What I really liked was the people there - always smiling, nice chatty conversations, helpful and courteous, asking how are you, how is your day, which makes for a comfortable feeling. Two things I wasn't crazy about (which the hotel and staff can't help) is 1) it's at least a 20 min drive to South Beach/Ocean Drive (and a $30 cab ride - one way!) and 2) the area the hotel is in is on a main, busy street, not one I'd like to walk around after dark. I will say that the hotel takes the fact that