<Author>nanner10
<Content>Convenient, reasonable, great service, hard to beat! Every once in a while you get a little more than you are expecting. We think that was the case for our Jan 06 stay at the Hampton Inn and Suites-Airport South-Blue Lagoon. For this recent cruise trip we wanted/needed to spend a little less for our room. I thought this review would help others in a similar situation.We were looking for a hotel in Miami for a one night pre-cruise stay. Our search and the recommendations we found (granted they were for some very nice hotels) kept pointing us toward a price point that was significantly more that we wanted to spend for 鈥渏ust a place to rest our bones for a few hours before the real vacation begins!鈥?We were looking for something close enough to the pier, with access to stores for those last minute cruise necessities (wink, wink) and a convenient place for dinner and a cocktail. While it would have been nice to be closer to the pier and more downtown, in reality, this hotel fit the bill very nicely.  This hotel is listed as a two star hotel. I can鈥檛 imagine why. Is it because it lacks its own restaurant? In my opinion and from the reviews I have read a number of other travelers agree with me that this hotel belongs firmly in the three star category 鈥?at least. While it is still a somewhat basic hotel, I feel that needs to be stated with a big qualification! From my own search I knew that many people seemed to be on the same quest, therefore, I arrived at this Hampton Inn knowing that I would pay much more careful attention to this hotel than I might ordinarily with the hope that I could write a review for travelers who had similar needs. The Hampton Inn and Suites Airport South-Blue Lagoon (what a mouthful!) seems well run, it is clean, quiet, well maintained and provides many extra services and throughout the hotel there are a multitude of little things that show an attention to detail that give the strong impression that someone really cares here! I haven鈥檛 seen that much lately!The Hampton Inn and Suites Airport South-Blue Lagoon offers;鈥oderately priced rooms: This is Miami folks! Decent rooms are not cheap here! The price depends on time of year, special rates such as AAA, AARP, etc. Our AAA rate room was $151.54 ($134.10 + $17.44 tax) on 1/20/06 鈥ree shuttle to/from the airport. Dial #366 from courtesy phones in luggage claim area. You will then need to go up to the 2nd floor (departures) and out to the sidewalk to catch the shuttle. It is easy to ID the shuttle: the entire shuttle bus has a multicolored patchwork painted on the sides with a Hampton Inn mural and says 鈥?7th Ave/Blue Lagoon鈥? Make sure you are on the correct Hampton Inn shuttle as there are multiple Hampton Inn locations in Miami!鈥?Free shuttle to nearby locations (our driver was Alvaro, who drove us to dinner at the nearby 94th Aero Squadron Restaurant and bar. From the bar we were able to watch planes come in for a landing.) The Host will call the hotel and the driver will come back for you when you are done鈥arking lot and garage: free for guests, $15 per day after check outTransportation to the cruise ship pier is not provided by the hotel, but they will call a taxi/shuttle for you:鈥axi $25 to cruise ship pier for two people鈥ndependent (non hotel) shuttle to the pier: $35 for two or $10pp for more than twoHOTEL鈥his hotel is located minutes from the airport, on a busy street. It is about 15 minutes (in light traffic) from the pier.鈥ery friendly, attentive, helpful and pleasant front desk staff (Thanks Yami and Pam!)鈥leasant lobby and grounds (being freshened up by groundskeepers while we were there)鈥?1 floors鈥ery quiet in room. Soundproofed windows. We were not disturbed by any street noise.鈥ur room did not have a Lagoon view, but, the city view toward pier was nice (with the exception of the parking lot and nearby medical building), especially at night.鈥afe. Room card was needed in elevators to access the guest floors鈥ell lit, quiet halls鈥mall, heated pool (felt just warm, but we did not go in) and hot tub (slightly green during our visit)鈥ool patio with a covered area with bistro tables and chairs. This was just outside the breakfast room. I would imagine you could take your breakfast outside.鈥n general this hotel has gone the extra step to provide an extra level of amenities, such as the rod to hang garment bags, the hairdryer with the added nightlight feature and the above average breakfast features. They have added many small touches that are easy to overlook, but show an attention to detail, such as the repeated use throughout the public areas and the guest rooms of the company logo on things like: toilet paper, glass panels and doors, shower curtains, bath mats, pillowcases, etc., even the cookies in your room! Nice touches.鈥omplimentary USA Today newspaperBUSINESS CENTER (just off the lobby)Multiple free computers with internet access and printer.Other business services availableIN HOTEL CONVENIENCE STORE (just off the lobby)Offering snacks, light foodBeverages, including beerMiscellaneous toiletries and OTC medicationsBREAKFAST ROOMOffers free coffee, tea, hot chocolate, OJ and apple juice, water, apples and bananas 24 hours a day.Free 鈥渙n the house鈥?breakfast includes the above items plus:French toast sticks, maple syrup, bagels, toast (toaster available) muffins, Danish pastries, biscuits (plain and cinnamon), sausages, fruit salad, 3 dry cold cereals, yogurt and oatmeal.Also offered are 鈥淥n the Run鈥?breakfasts. They provide a rack of pre-selected breakfast items packaged in a brown bag, just grab and go.EXERCISE ROOMDid not use! Appears well equippedROOM鈥reshly painted soft golden walls鈥icely decorated with nice art鈥ppears recently decorated with newer bedding, etc. The rug was very slightly worn.鈥eating area, small table two chairs鈥esk, armoire鈥edium Cherry finish furniture, some with contrasting walnut trim, rubbed bronze light fixtures.鈥added lap desk/bed table鈥wo phones鈥nternet connection/wireless, printer services available (sent from room to front desk)鈥ree local calls. Also free connection to a long distance carrier (long distance rates then apply)鈥intendo鈥tandard TV channels with 3 HBO channels鈥roning board/iron鈥offeemaker, coffee and tea, cookies etc.鈥lectronic safe in the closet鈥loset door has full length mirror鈥easonably comfortable mattress (and we are picky!)鈥ots of pillows鈥itted sheets 鈥 post mounted to wall to hang garment bags鈥tationary wood bench for luggageBATH鈥lean 鈥ell lit鈥?/2 circle shower rod鈥ile floor鈥ubtle wallpaper鈥unbean Brightsaver hairdryer with built in nightlight 鈥ath products; shampoo, lotion, conditioner, etc.鈥xtra large vanity鈥assage showerhead with good water pressure鈥ecorative towelsNEARBYThe neighborhood seems to be reasonably safe, with usual precautions advised. In the immediate area are: CVS, Walgreens, McDonalds, Wendy鈥檚, Burger King, Pollo Tropical (chicken restaurant) and a gas station. Across the street from the hotel is a small strip mall (Air Park Plaza) that houses: Publix (grocery store chain that carries beer and wine), full liquor store, Don Bon, a Cuban restaurant, pizza restaurant, subway, Expo Center (Home Depot, if I had known, I might have stayed here just for that!), a shoe store, a hair and nail salon and a party store.Needless to say we would recommend this hotel and would stay here again. 
